---
const repoUrl = 'https://github.com/acoyfellow/flue-snippets';
---

<section class="hero">
  <h1>Flue on Cloudflare</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    You already know Cloudflare Workers. <a href="https://flueframework.com">Flue</a> is the
    agent harness that sits on top — turning a Worker into a programmable, Claude-Code-shaped
    agent runtime. This page walks through four working agents, smallest to largest, to show
    how the two fit together.
  </p>
  <a class="badge" href={repoUrl}>View the source →</a>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 1rem 0 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .lede a {
    color: var(--cf-orange);
  }
</style>
